comments.text:
God blessed you with a GREAT MOM Kevin! You seem like such a great man. I know we have our flaws. But gotta say, this is touching. I started out crushing it until surgeries destroyed my body. I still thank God that my then 20 year old son stepped up big time to take over the day to day operations and he’s 40 now and I live in constant chronic pain. My wife and I opened our first of two flooring stores in 1990 and I don’t know with how we have devalued the currency here how long we’re going to keep crushing it but now my sister in-law who lives with us but is dying likely before she leaves the hospital and mom is 90 and in 4th Stage Alzheimer’s and doesn’t even remember her oldest daughter from day to day until she gets near her but she forgets everything. I want to secure my families legacy and diversify into rental properties but I’m barely functioning and we were desperate for warehouse space and we did buy a $2 million dollar warehouse this year but this was before we finally got them to move back here and we weren’t aware of my sisters cancer returning and either was she. They give her maybe 14 months or zero if her emaciated body could even withstand chemo and radiation again. Without it, they give her 8 months. Meanwhile I have cash in the bank that’s going to be wallpaper soon if this doesn’t get straightened out and it can’t without me and I’m at a loss because I don’t want to go into pain management but no doctor knows what to do because I’ve literally destroyed my skeletal system and live with severe headaches that I can fake I feel alright for only so long. But we may have to people we love dying so soon, it’d thrown a wrench into everything. I have some metals and we have an LLC we pay rent to through the now 3 buildings we purchased and are doing very well. But that’s our only revenue stream ever since I had a failed neck surgery. I can’t barely walk when I get up for a few hours after a hot shower. I was 26 and bulletproof when we opened the first store and 10/12 hour days 6 days a week were normal until the man who taught me the trade came to work because I could sell way more than I could install in a day.  But I had to have someone I trusted. 
I gotta say because I may lose my sister in-law and with mom in-law who I’ve literally known longer than my mom who died at 74, and I’ve spent much more time with my in-laws with her at 90 now and falling all the time, she’s been such a rock in my life that this is over the top too much. But I’ve been home a lot by myself thinking because I feel so miserable, but I’ve shed more tears over the knee still here and my own mom and dad than I have in over a decade. 
Thanks for showing your humanity to me and everyone who sees this. I have to find a way to get that money working for me before it’s kindling!
Be blessed Mr. Wonderful.
